# libm_gen: Configurable sinf Code-Gen Pipeline

Generates RISC-V soft-float `sinf` assembly (and its `cosf` path) from a
TOML config describing the target microarchitecture, polynomial shape, and
reduction strategy.

## Prerequisites

- Python >= 3.11 (for `tomllib`)
- [Sollya](https://www.sollya.org/) on `PATH` (for non-baseline configs)
- Andes RV32 toolchain (for `make test-sinf`)
- QEMU / FPGA board (for benchmarks)

## Quick start

```sh
# Run from libm/machine/riscv/
cd libm/machine/riscv

# Sanity check: reproduce GoFast baseline (no Sollya needed)
python tools/libm_gen/gen_sinf.py tools/libm_gen/configs/baseline.toml
# Diff the generated coeff table against the original:
diff gen/baseline/andes_fpsincof.s andes_fpsincof.s
# Test the generated assembly:
make GEN=baseline test-sinf

# New config with Sollya-computed degree-9 minimax coefficients:
python tools/libm_gen/gen_sinf.py tools/libm_gen/configs/d9_estrin2.toml
make GEN=d9_estrin2 test-sinf

# Full pipeline (gen + test + bench + report):
python tools/libm_gen/run_experiment.py tools/libm_gen/configs/d9_estrin2.toml

# Sweep mode (all configs in a directory):
python tools/libm_gen/run_experiment.py tools/libm_gen/configs/sweep/
# Results in gen/sweep.csv
```

## Config schema (TOML)

Key sections:

| Section | Key | Description |
|---------|-----|-------------|
| top | `name` | Unique ID; output goes to `gen/<name>/` |
| top | `function` | `sinf` (cosf/tanf planned) |
| `[kernel]` | `sin_degree` | Odd degree: 7, 9, 11 |
| `[kernel]` | `cos_degree` | Even degree: 8, 10, 12 |
| `[kernel]` | `evaluation` | `horner`, `estrin2`, `estrin4` |
| `[kernel]` | `unroll` | `true` = no loop; `false` = sentinel loop |
| `[reduction]` | `strategy` | `bit_serial` (others planned) |
| `[reduction]` | `huge_arg_policy` | `return_nan` or `reduce` |
| `[coeffs_override]` | `sin_q31` / `cos_q31` | Bypass Sollya (baseline only) |

See `configs/baseline.toml` for a fully annotated example.

## Output files (`gen/<name>/`)

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `sf_sin.s` | Main `sinf` kernel (replaces `sf_sin.s`) |
| `andes_fpsincof.s` | Sin coefficient table |
| `andes_fpcoscof.s` | Cos coefficient table |
| `andes_fpreduct.s` | Argument reduction (replaces `andes_fpreduct.s`) |
| `coeffs.json` | Computed coefficients + Sollya supnorm |
| `config.toml` | Config snapshot for reproducibility |
| `report.json` | Accuracy, size, and cycle-count results (after run_experiment.py) |

## Q1.31 polynomial arithmetic

The kernel uses `mulhu` (upper 32 bits of 32x32 unsigned multiply) throughout.
After `__gf_fpreduct`, x^2 is in Q0.32 format (value = register / 2^32).
Each Horner step: `acc = c[k] - mulhu(x2, acc)` where all `c[k]` are Q1.31
integers (= coefficient * 2^31). The constant term c[0] >= 2^31 acts as the
loop sentinel (MSB set) in looped Horner mode.

Sollya computes `fpminimax(sin(sqrt(u))/sqrt(u), [|0,1,...,n|], [|DD,...|], [0,(pi/4)^2])`
and the generator converts each floating-point coefficient to Q1.31 via
`round(abs(coeff) * 2^31)`.

## Makefile integration

```sh
make GEN=<name> test-sinf   # accuracy test (opt vs ref diff)
make GEN=<name> bench-sinf  # cycle count on FPGA via GDB
make GEN=<name> size-sinf   # .text size
```

The `GEN=` override replaces `sf_sin.s`, `andes_fpreduct.s`,
`andes_fpsincof.s`, and `andes_fpcoscof.s` with the generated versions
from `gen/<name>/`. All other assembly is unchanged.
